metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #66
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Elevation #241
metadata.description:
There‚Äôs so much more to our world than what we are able to perceive, let alone understand. Will we ever be able to even fully understand ourselves?

‚Äì

Elevation is a series of 320 generative elevation drawings of imaginary structures. It is a reminder of the limits of our consciousness, and an ode to the manifold nuances that lie beyond what we can perceive, beyond what we even can imagine.

As a generative artist, I aim to elevate my own consciousness with the help of the machine. I welcome algorithms and randomness into the creation of my works, taking full control, and intentionally giving it away, always seeking to expand my imagination. For as humans alone, we remain limited to our own edifice of thought, and often fail to free ourselves from the visible, mundane world.

Both are present in Elevation: the visible and the imaginary, the mundane and the transcendent, the solid and the fragile. Where an architect‚Äôs elevation drawing marks the transition from the thought world into the visible world, Elevation remains in-between, depicting both the idea of an imaginary structure, and the structure itself.

‚Äì

Elevation is intended for print. All holders of an Elevation NFT will be able to order the corresponding signed print in the respective paper format via andreasrau.eu/elevation. Press [s] to save the image as displayed or [p] to generate a print-ready PNG image at 300 dpi. This might take a while, depending on paper format and your hardware.

‚Äì

Elevation
p5.js, glsl, html, css
Andreas Rau, 2022

metadata.name: Kinetograms #261
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: inter(rupt)ions #20
metadata.description:
"Taking into account the fact that everything and everyone is made of atoms, then all living things and objects are breakable. But what about the things that are not tangible? How do they break? 'inter(rupt)ions' is an interpretation and visualization of a good feeling, being broken, separated and shaped into lines and geometric forms, whether that feeling is trust, hope, respect or love."

AI on canvas (2022)

metadata.name: Paper Mandala #54
metadata.description:
A collaboration with P1xelboy and Paper Buddha.
Beautiful paper mandalas made purely with code in Paper Buddha's style.
Features include:
27 different palettes
3 different mandala types (Lotus, Starburst Style 1 and Starburst Style 2)
Four sections of the mandala with one of 10 different pattern types (Dots, Checks, Crosses, Triangles, Stripes, Circles, Polygons, Lazers, Quadrants and Hatching)
4 different direction types of shadow - of varying length
Randomly placed star background
Randomly placed Nebula
Possible Special Pattern Effect with darker stippling pattern
Possible Nirvana Effect where random colors are added to one of either Golden, Silver, Bronze, Blue Moon or Sea Green palettes.

Using only code, this produces a unique output which does take a few seconds to load.
Press "S" to Save your unique Paper Mandala as a 2048 x 2048 JPG
Press "R" for a random shuffle effect - (please wait for reload) - Refresh page to reset

The project works in a responsive browser, so to set up for phone background or watch, resize the browser accordingly and Alt + Print Screen to get an appropriately sized image.

Offered as a Dutch Auction, holders of the first 20 tokens (1-20) will receive additional benefits in the form of utility for future releases in the P1xelboy/Paper Mandala collaboration series. (exact details to be determined)
This utility will remain attached to tokens 1-20 and transfer to the new owner upon subsequent secondary sales.

Uses p5.js and p5.pattern
@p1x3lboy @paperbuddha - September 2022

metadata.name: Dencity #152
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ‚ù§Ô∏è, code and p5js.

metadata.name: drawz fxh_t019 #23
metadata.description:
'drawz' fxh_t019 is also vanilla javascript template for fxhash


feel free, to use (parts of) it, and learn from the source.
and use it as a start for your own creative projects and adventures

This version has some extra routines you can use; 
and a lot of comments in the source


A cleaned up - smaller version; just doing the basic tech screen & window-handeling etc. with just drawing dots can be found here.
(and older and newer updated versions)
https://elout.home.xs4all.nl/drawz/


Mostly I start with a clean template; 
then add: copy-paste routines into it. Things I want to use; sprites, text-font, filters, lines, 3D etc. 
Like kinda lego blocks. Some routines I re-use for 30 years now. 
Although often they have changed over time.


Vanilla javascript - And directly control your rgb buffer
-------------------------------------------------------------------
cons:
- can be overwhelming for starting coders compared to p5js
- you have to write / use and tinker with new drawing routines by yourself. 
- still can be optimized a lot, and run much faster
-- (feel free to do that! - release new versions yourself)
- I just coded it in Notepad++ and tested it in a browser.
- I have no experience with git-hub, or those other nifty tools
- I'm more an Artist than a coder, still learning new things as well.
- I have my own 'old' coding style I picked up ages ago, and still use now and then. Started with basic and Z80a as a teenager.
- for sure there are still some stupid bugs, spelling errors in it  ^___^

pros:
- fxtemplate - fxpreview when done drawing / splash-screen support on top; while drawing.
- do like 4000 x 4000 images on safari; on an old Iphone 5
- just 1 index.html now - small file size: 
- the source of the 'cleaned-up' version is now 34b (not minified, and still comments in the source; can be even smaller)
- direct control of the RGB buffer; every pixel.
- I added some basic routines, like drawing points, lines, squares, sprite-brushes, filters, and my pixel-font
- draw, add-mix or subtract - manipulate every pixel how you wish
- I work with a big off-screen kind of image; a rgb-buffer; so drawing goes 'mucho' faster and render it to a screen-scaled image.
- no other libraries used
----------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image 

- The work will refresh and restart after some time

Save image - with s-key 
(includes the fxhash key-seed and num# of the follow-up images)
--- It can take some seconds before the saving happens; 
--- the browser has to handle (very) large MB .png files first 
--- before it can save them 

- splash image support - to hide drawing at start
- redraw the image after a while; or not.
- mouse position check for the bigger image
- fps counter for testing etc.
----------------------------------------------------------------
written in vanilla JavaScript, more info in the source-code


drawz - latest or an updated version can be found at.
https://elout.home.xs4all.nl/drawz/

It would be nice; to include more routines into it
in the future.

And instead of 1 big library with everything in it
I would like to have these templates; 
where you can add different little snippets and routines 
that you want to use into it, and start playing next.
Still learning new things as well. And getting inspired.

I don't mind people to use the tech-source as a start for their own projects. 

But the palette, and composition & structure build-up; is mine. 
Don't change just 1 or 2 -things then re-release it.

If you want to release something of your own,
your sketch and generative work; really should look total different!
You can use the technics to draw new things,
but you have to start from scratch again; 
choosing points, lines etc. to play with and go from there.
Enjoy! 


-for the love of Art and jumping in rain puddles-

'like jimi and guitar'  0__.  ^____^


xxx  amsterdam  chillout

September 29, 2022

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #182
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Introspection #146
metadata.description:
Sketches of geometric shapes with scale symmetry.

"What does the mirror see when it looks in the mirror?"

--

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "S" to export a standard resolution image.
- Press "P" to export an hi-res image.
- Press "G" to toggle the grain.

metadata.name: Cradle #82
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
